                            <comment id="13972334" author="djencks" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2014 06:03:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This appears to be a framework problem, if you call context.getService(ServiceReference) on a service reference that has been unregistered.  The code in Felix is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;S&amp;gt; S getService(Bundle bundle, ServiceReference&amp;lt;S&amp;gt; ref)&lt;br/&gt;
    {&lt;br/&gt;
        try&lt;/p&gt;
        {
            return (S) m_registry.getService(bundle, ref);
        }
&lt;p&gt;        catch (ServiceException ex)&lt;/p&gt;
        {
            fireFrameworkEvent(FrameworkEvent.ERROR, ref.getBundle(), ex);
        }

&lt;p&gt;        return null;&lt;br/&gt;
    }&lt;br/&gt;
and if ref is unregistered then ref.getBundle() must return null.  Could we use the ref as the source instead of the missing bundle in this case?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
